<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bpmn:definitions xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:bpmn="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/MODEL" xmlns:bpmndi="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/DI" xmlns:dc="http://www.omg.org/spec/DD/20100524/DC" xmlns:di="http://www.omg.org/spec/DD/20100524/DI" xmlns:zeebe="http://camunda.org/schema/zeebe/1.0" xmlns:camunda="http://camunda.org/schema/1.0/bpmn" id="Definitions_IdealState_v10" targetNamespace="http://sla.governance/bpmn/onboarding" exporter="Camunda Modeler" exporterVersion="5.44.0">
  <bpmn:collaboration id="Collaboration_IdealState_v10">
    <bpmn:participant id="Participant_Enterprise" name="Software Onboarding" processRef="Process_Onboarding_v10" />
  </bpmn:collaboration>
  <bpmn:process id="Process_Onboarding_v10" name="Product Management — Software Onboarding v10 (Camunda 8)" isExecutable="true">
    <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="GW_TriageDecision" name="Approved ?" default="Flow_v5_4">
      <bpmn:incoming>Flow_v5_2</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_v5_4</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_1iblw95</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
    <bpmn:endEvent id="End_Rejected" name="Request&#10;Rejected">
      <bpmn:incoming>Flow_v5_4</bpmn:incoming>
    </bpmn:endEvent>
    <bpmn:subProcess id="SP_RequestTriage" name="Refine Request">
      <bpmn:incoming>Flow_1xhs1a0</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_v5_2</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:startEvent id="SP1_Start">
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_SP1_1</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:startEvent>
      <bpmn:userTask id="Task_ReviewExisting" name="Review problem and existing&#10;solutions">
        <bpmn:documentation>Review the organization's existing software portfolio and backlog to determine whether current solutions can fulfill the identified business need. Search the enterprise software catalog, asset management system, and approved vendor registry for existing capabilities that overlap with the request. Assess whether existing licenses, modules, or configurations can be leveraged before initiating a new procurement or build effort.</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:formDefinition formId="sp1-review-existing" />
          <zeebe:assignmentDefinition candidateGroups="business-lane" />
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="topics" value="Intake" />
            <zeebe:property name="comments" value="REGULATORY CONTROLS: (1) OCC 2023-17 Section 20: Inventory management — the organization must maintain an accurate inventory of all third-party relationships; this review ensures new requests are checked against the existing portfolio to avoid duplicate vendor relationships and unmanaged concentration risk. (2) NIST CSF 2.0 ID.AM (Asset Management): Verify existing software assets are cataloged, classified, and their capabilities documented to enable effective reuse analysis. (3) SOX Section 404: Ensure any software reuse decision is documented with rationale to maintain an auditable trail of technology decisions impacting financial controls. EVIDENCE COLLECTION: (a) Search results from enterprise software catalog showing existing solutions evaluated. (b) Portfolio overlap analysis documenting how existing tools were assessed against the new requirement. (c) Decision rationale document if existing solution is deemed sufficient (bypass path) or insufficient (proceed to formal process). (d) Asset management system query log showing search criteria used. DATA POINTS: Request description, business unit, existing software matches found (name, version, license status, utilization rate), gap analysis summary (what the existing solution covers vs. what is missing), requester assessment of fit (sufficient/insufficient), estimated cost avoidance if existing solution is leveraged." />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_r" value="Business" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_a" value="Business" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_c" value="Governance" />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_SP1_1</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_0ccvusw</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>
      <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="GW_BypassProcess" name="Existing&#10;Solution ?">
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_0ccvusw</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_SP1_Yes</bpmn:outgoing>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_0p7pllp</bpmn:outgoing>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_15fp02f</bpmn:outgoing>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_0y548b1</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
      <bpmn:userTask id="Task_LeverageExisting" name="Leverage existing&#10;software">
        <bpmn:documentation>Configure, extend, or activate existing software capabilities to meet the identified business need without initiating a new procurement. This may involve enabling dormant modules, adjusting configurations, requesting additional user licenses, or integrating existing tools in a new workflow. Document the reuse decision and update the software asset register to reflect the expanded usage scope.</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:formDefinition formId="sp1-leverage-existing" />
          <zeebe:assignmentDefinition candidateGroups="business-lane" />
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="topics" value="Intake" />
            <zeebe:property name="comments" value="REGULATORY CONTROLS: (1) OCC 2023-17 Section 20: Even when leveraging existing software, the expanded scope of use must be evaluated for any change in risk profile — if the existing vendor relationship is being extended to new data types, business functions, or user populations, the third-party risk assessment may need updating. (2) NIST CSF 2.0 PR.DS (Data Security): Ensure data protection controls remain adequate for the expanded use case — new data flows or user populations may require additional access controls or encryption. (3) SOX Section 404: Document the decision to reuse existing software with clear rationale, cost avoidance calculation, and any changes to financial control configurations. EVIDENCE COLLECTION: (a) Reuse decision document with business justification and cost avoidance estimate. (b) Updated software asset register entry reflecting expanded scope. (c) License compliance verification confirming sufficient licenses for expanded use. (d) Configuration change request (if applicable) with approval chain. (e) Risk assessment delta — confirmation that expanded use does not change the vendor&#39;s risk tier. DATA POINTS: Existing software name and version, current license count vs. required, configuration changes needed, estimated cost avoidance vs. new procurement, risk tier impact assessment (no change/escalation needed), expanded user population scope, new data types introduced (if any)." />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_r" value="Business" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_a" value="Business" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_c" value="Governance" />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_SP1_Yes</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_SP1_EndLev</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>
      <bpmn:endEvent id="End_Leveraged" name="Software&#10;Leveraged">
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_SP1_EndLev</bpmn:incoming>
      </bpmn:endEvent>
      <bpmn:userTask id="Task_GatherDocs" name="Gather&#10;documentation">
        <bpmn:documentation>Form: vendor-intake-form.html Sections 1-2 (Request Basics + Governance) — business persona view. Assemble all documentation required to support a formal software request submission. Gather business requirements, use cases, stakeholder sign-offs, budget authorization, data classification assessment, and any preliminary market research. Ensure the request package is complete per the standardized intake template to prevent delays during triage. Information collected here is centralized and reused throughout the lifecycle.</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:formDefinition formId="sp1-gather-documentation" />
          <zeebe:assignmentDefinition candidateGroups="business-lane" />
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="topics" value="Intake, Funding, Privacy" />
            <zeebe:property name="comments" value="REGULATORY CONTROLS: (1) OCC 2023-17 Section 25: Needs assessment documentation — the business case must articulate the need, alternatives considered, and alignment with the organization&#39;s strategic plan. This documentation becomes part of the regulatory examination file for third-party risk management. (2) GDPR Article 35/CCPA: If the software will process personal data, a preliminary Data Protection Impact Assessment (DPIA) screening should be initiated at this stage to identify high-risk processing activities early. (3) SOX Section 404: Budget authorization and financial justification must follow the organization&#39;s delegated authority matrix and be documented for audit trail purposes. (4) NIST CSF 2.0 GV.RM (Risk Management Strategy): Preliminary risk indicators should be captured to enable early risk tier estimation. EVIDENCE COLLECTION: (a) Completed software request intake form per standardized template. (b) Business requirements document with use cases and success criteria. (c) Stakeholder sign-off confirming business need and sponsorship. (d) Budget authorization or funding source identification. (e) Preliminary data classification assessment (what data types will the software process). (f) Market research or preliminary vendor identification (if available). (g) DPIA screening questionnaire (if personal data processing is involved). DATA POINTS: Business unit, cost center, budget amount authorized, expected user count, data types to be processed (PII, PHI, financial, public), deployment model preference (cloud/on-premise/hybrid), integration requirements with existing systems, urgency level, strategic alignment score, compliance requirements identified." />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_r" value="Business" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_a" value="Business" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_c" value="Finance, Privacy" />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_SP1_CG_No</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_01gazr0</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_SP1_3</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>
      <bpmn:userTask id="Task_SubmitRequest" name="Submit software&#10;request">
        <bpmn:documentation>Form: vendor-intake-form.html Section 5 (Review and Submit). Submit the completed software request package to the Product Management team for formal triage and evaluation. The submission must include all required documentation per the intake template. Upon submission, the request is assigned a tracking number and enters the governance workflow with full audit trail from this point forward.</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:formDefinition formId="sp1-submit-request" />
          <zeebe:assignmentDefinition candidateGroups="business-lane" />
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="topics" value="Intake" />
            <zeebe:property name="comments" value="REGULATORY CONTROLS: (1) OCC 2023-17 Section 25: Formal submission creates the official record of the third-party engagement request — this is the point at which the governance audit trail formally begins. The submission must be timestamped and immutable once submitted. (2) NIST CSF 2.0 GV.OC (Organizational Context): The request must capture sufficient context about the business need, data sensitivity, and operational criticality to enable accurate downstream risk assessment and pathway routing. (3) SOX Section 302: The submitting business owner certifies the accuracy and completeness of the request documentation, creating accountability for the information provided. EVIDENCE COLLECTION: (a) Submitted request package with timestamp, submitter identity, and completeness validation result. (b) Tracking number assignment confirmation. (c) Acknowledgment receipt from Product Management confirming request received. (d) Completeness check result (all required fields populated per intake template). (e) Submitter certification that information is accurate and complete. DATA POINTS: Request tracking number, submission timestamp, submitter name and role, business unit, completeness score (percentage of template fields populated), attachments list, priority requested by business, estimated annual cost, data classification summary." />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_r" value="Business" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_a" value="Business" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_c" value="Governance" />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_SP1_MergeSubmit</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_SP1_4</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>
      <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="GW_MergeSubmit">
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_SP1_3</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_15fp02f</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_SP1_MergeSubmit</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_SP1_MergeSubmit" sourceRef="GW_MergeSubmit" targetRef="Task_SubmitRequest" />
      <bpmn:userTask id="Task_InitialTriage" name="Initial Triage&#10;and Evaluation">
        <bpmn:documentation>Form: vendor-intake-form.html (read-only view of submitted data). Perform initial triage of the incoming software request to evaluate feasibility, strategic alignment, duplicate detection, and resource availability. Includes automated pre-screening for known vendor matches and existing capability overlap. Assign preliminary priority and determine whether the request should proceed, be rejected, or be returned for additional information. This is the first governance gate in the onboarding lifecycle.</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:formDefinition formId="sp1-initial-triage" />
          <zeebe:assignmentDefinition candidateGroups="business-lane" />
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="topics" value="Intake, Compliance, TPRM" />
            <zeebe:property name="comments" value="REGULATORY CONTROLS: (1) OCC 2023-17 Section 25-30: Initial risk screening — determine whether the proposed software/vendor relationship would create concentration risk, introduce critical dependency, or fall within a high-risk category requiring enhanced due diligence. Early identification of critical/significant third-party relationships. (2) NIST CSF 2.0 GV.RM-01: Risk management strategy alignment — verify the request aligns with the organization&#39;s risk appetite and technology strategy. (3) SOX Section 404: Ensure the triage decision is documented with rationale, supporting the auditability of the intake process. Delegated authority verified for the approval to proceed. EVIDENCE COLLECTION: (a) Triage evaluation form with scoring across feasibility, strategic alignment, duplicate detection, and resource availability. (b) Duplicate detection results from software catalog and vendor registry search. (c) Preliminary risk screening result (concentration risk, criticality assessment). (d) Triage decision with documented rationale (approve/reject/return for info). (e) Priority assignment with justification. (f) Assigned governance analyst name and date. DATA POINTS: Request tracking number, triage score (composite), strategic alignment rating (1-5), duplicate match results (existing solutions found), preliminary risk indicators, resource availability assessment, triage decision (approve/reject/return), decision rationale, assigned analyst, triage completion timestamp, SLA compliance (within 2-day target)." />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_r" value="Business" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_a" value="Governance" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_c" value="Compliance, TPRM" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_i" value="" />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_SP1_6</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_SP1_5</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>
      <bpmn:endEvent id="End_TriageSLAEscalation" name="Triage SLA&#10;Escalation">
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_SP1_SLA</bpmn:incoming>
      </bpmn:endEvent>
      <bpmn:userTask id="Task_ClassifyRequest" name="Classify&#10;Request">
        <bpmn:documentation>Classify the software request by type: Defined Need (standard procurement with clear requirements), Forced Update (mandatory vendor/regulatory-driven change), or Speculative (exploratory/innovation request for idea funnel). Classification drives downstream routing, required approvals, and process depth.</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:formDefinition formId="sp1-classify-request" />
          <zeebe:assignmentDefinition candidateGroups="governance-lane" />
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="topics" value="Intake" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_r" value="Governance" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_a" value="Governance" />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_SP1_4</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_SP1_6</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>
      <bpmn:serviceTask id="SendTask_SP1Complete" name="SP1&#10;Notification">
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:taskDefinition type="status-notification" />
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="phase" value="SP1_Complete" />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_SP1_5</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_SP1_Notify</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:serviceTask>
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_SP1_Notify" sourceRef="SendTask_SP1Complete" targetRef="SP1_End" />
      <bpmn:endEvent id="SP1_End" name="Triage&#10;Complete">
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_SP1_Notify</bpmn:incoming>
      </bpmn:endEvent>
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_SP1_1" sourceRef="SP1_Start" targetRef="Task_ReviewExisting" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_SP1_Yes" name="Yes" sourceRef="GW_BypassProcess" targetRef="Task_LeverageExisting">
        <bpmn:conditionExpression xsi:type="bpmn:tFormalExpression">=true</bpmn:conditionExpression>
      </bpmn:sequenceFlow>
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_SP1_EndLev" sourceRef="Task_LeverageExisting" targetRef="End_Leveraged" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_SP1_3" sourceRef="Task_GatherDocs" targetRef="GW_MergeSubmit" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_SP1_4" sourceRef="Task_SubmitRequest" targetRef="Task_CompletenessGate" />
      <bpmn:userTask id="Task_CompletenessGate" name="Completeness&#10;Gate">
        <bpmn:documentation>Validate that the submitted software request meets all minimum completeness requirements before proceeding to classification and triage. Check for problem statement quality, business owner identification, urgency rating, and all required intake fields.</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:formDefinition formId="sp1-completeness-gate" />
          <zeebe:assignmentDefinition candidateGroups="automation-lane" />
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="topics" value="Intake" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_r" value="Automation" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_a" value="Governance" />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_SP1_4</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_SP1_CG1</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>
      <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="GW_Complete" name="Complete?">
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_SP1_CG1</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_SP1_CG_Yes</bpmn:outgoing>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_SP1_CG_No</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_SP1_CG1" sourceRef="Task_CompletenessGate" targetRef="GW_Complete" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_SP1_CG_Yes" name="Yes" sourceRef="GW_Complete" targetRef="Task_ClassifyRequest">
        <bpmn:conditionExpression xsi:type="bpmn:tFormalExpression">=completenessDecision = "Complete"</bpmn:conditionExpression>
      </bpmn:sequenceFlow>
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_SP1_CG_No" name="No" sourceRef="GW_Complete" targetRef="Task_GatherDocs">
        <bpmn:conditionExpression xsi:type="bpmn:tFormalExpression">=completenessDecision = "Incomplete"</bpmn:conditionExpression>
      </bpmn:sequenceFlow>
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_SP1_6" sourceRef="Task_ClassifyRequest" targetRef="Task_DealKillerCheck" />
      <bpmn:businessRuleTask id="Task_DealKillerCheck" name="Deal Killer&#10;Pre-Screen">
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:calledDecision decisionId="OB_DMN_DealKillerPrescreen" resultVariable="dealKillerResult" />
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="topics" value="Intake, Compliance" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_r" value="Automation" />
            <zeebe:property name="raci_a" value="Governance" />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_SP1_6</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_SP1_DK1</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:businessRuleTask>
      <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="GW_DealKiller" name="Deal Killer?">
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_SP1_DK1</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_SP1_DK_No</bpmn:outgoing>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_SP1_DK_Yes</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
      <bpmn:endEvent id="End_DealKiller" name="Deal Killer&#10;Blocked">
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_SP1_DK_Yes</bpmn:incoming>
      </bpmn:endEvent>
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_SP1_DK1" sourceRef="Task_DealKillerCheck" targetRef="GW_DealKiller" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_SP1_DK_No" name="No" sourceRef="GW_DealKiller" targetRef="Task_InitialTriage">
        <bpmn:conditionExpression xsi:type="bpmn:tFormalExpression">=dealKillerResult = "Proceed"</bpmn:conditionExpression>
      </bpmn:sequenceFlow>
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_SP1_DK_Yes" name="Yes" sourceRef="GW_DealKiller" targetRef="End_DealKiller">
        <bpmn:conditionExpression xsi:type="bpmn:tFormalExpression">=dealKillerResult = "Blocked"</bpmn:conditionExpression>
      </bpmn:sequenceFlow>
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_SP1_5" sourceRef="Task_InitialTriage" targetRef="SendTask_SP1Complete" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_SP1_SLA" sourceRef="Timer_TriageSLA" targetRef="End_TriageSLAEscalation" />
      <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="Gateway_132net7" name="Mini RFP&#10;Required?">
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_0j4a2xs</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_0f1ym01</bpmn:outgoing>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_0kh8omi</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
      <bpmn:subProcess id="Activity_0j7ifzh" name="Mini RFP&#10;Pre-Screen">
        <bpmn:incoming>Flow_0f1ym01</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_1c4ei9u</bpmn:outgoing>
        <bpmn:startEvent id="Event_1xcpf6u">
          <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_02obvfw</bpmn:outgoing>
        </bpmn:startEvent>
        <bpmn:userTask id="Activity_1jd4o1m" name="Step 1:&#10;Understand&#10;the Need">
          <bpmn:extensionElements>
            <zeebe:formDefinition formId="rfp-step1-understand-need" />
            <zeebe:assignmentDefinition candidateGroups="business-lane" />
            <zeebe:properties>
              <zeebe:property name="topics" value="Mini RFP" />
              <zeebe:property name="raci_r" value="Business" />
              <zeebe:property name="raci_a" value="Business" />
            </zeebe:properties>
          </bpmn:extensionElements>
          <bpmn:incoming>Flow_02obvfw</bpmn:incoming>
          <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_06ks9ue</bpmn:outgoing>
        </bpmn:userTask>
        <bpmn:userTask id="Activity_07qg27e" name="Step 2:&#10;Vendor&#10;Context">
          <bpmn:extensionElements>
            <zeebe:formDefinition formId="rfp-step2-vendor-context" />
            <zeebe:assignmentDefinition candidateGroups="business-lane" />
            <zeebe:properties>
              <zeebe:property name="topics" value="Mini RFP" />
              <zeebe:property name="raci_r" value="Business" />
              <zeebe:property name="raci_a" value="Business" />
            </zeebe:properties>
          </bpmn:extensionElements>
          <bpmn:incoming>Flow_06ks9ue</bpmn:incoming>
          <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_1siy0gl</bpmn:outgoing>
        </bpmn:userTask>
        <bpmn:userTask id="Activity_0uolphp" name="Step 2.5:&#10;Classification&#10;Check">
          <bpmn:extensionElements>
            <zeebe:formDefinition formId="rfp-step2b-classification-validation" />
            <zeebe:assignmentDefinition candidateGroups="governance-lane" />
            <zeebe:properties>
              <zeebe:property name="topics" value="Mini RFP, Classification" />
              <zeebe:property name="raci_r" value="Governance" />
              <zeebe:property name="raci_a" value="Governance" />
              <zeebe:property name="raci_c" value="Business" />
            </zeebe:properties>
          </bpmn:extensionElements>
          <bpmn:incoming>Flow_1siy0gl</bpmn:incoming>
          <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_0z8ekq0</bpmn:outgoing>
        </bpmn:userTask>
        <bpmn:businessRuleTask id="Activity_0qm2dwv" name="Deal-Killer&#10;Pre-Screen">
          <bpmn:extensionElements>
            <zeebe:calledDecision decisionId="OB-DMN-7-deal-killer-prescreen" resultVariable="dealKillerResult" />
          </bpmn:extensionElements>
          <bpmn:incoming>Flow_0z8ekq0</bpmn:incoming>
          <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_1113k7p</bpmn:outgoing>
        </bpmn:businessRuleTask>
        <bpmn:exclusiveGateway id="Gateway_15kvflp" name="Deal Killers&#10;Clear?" default="Flow_0lt8pon">
          <bpmn:incoming>Flow_1113k7p</bpmn:incoming>
          <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_1btvpel</bpmn:outgoing>
          <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_0lt8pon</bpmn:outgoing>
        </bpmn:exclusiveGateway>
        <bpmn:userTask id="Activity_0h9zvjd" name="Step 3:&#10;Deal-Killer&#10;Results">
          <bpmn:extensionElements>
            <zeebe:formDefinition formId="rfp-step3-deal-killer" />
            <zeebe:assignmentDefinition candidateGroups="business-lane" />
            <zeebe:properties>
